#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:32
msgid "Mitigation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:34
msgid ""
"When PR_SET_L1D_FLUSH is enabled for a task a flush of the L1D cache is "
"performed when the task is scheduled out and the incoming task belongs to a "
"different process and therefore to a different address space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:38
msgid ""
"If the underlying CPU supports L1D flushing in hardware, the hardware "
"mechanism is used, software fallback for the mitigation, is not supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:42
msgid "Mitigation control on the kernel command line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:44
msgid ""
"The kernel command line allows to control the L1D flush mitigations at boot "
"time with the option \"l1d_flush=\". The valid arguments for this option are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:48
msgid "on"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:48
msgid ""
"Enables the prctl interface, applications trying to use the prctl() will "
"fail with an error if l1d_flush is not enabled"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:53
msgid "By default the mechanism is disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:56
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:58
msgid ""
"The mechanism does not mitigate L1D data leaks between tasks belonging to "
"different processes which are concurrently executing on sibling threads of a "
"physical CPU core when SMT is enabled on the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:62
msgid ""
"This can be addressed by controlled placement of processes on physical CPU "
"cores or by disabling SMT. See the relevant chapter in the L1TF mitigation "
"document: :ref:`Documentation/admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1tf.rst <smt_control>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/l1d_flush.rst:66
msgid ""
"**NOTE** : The opt-in of a task for L1D flushing works only when the task's "
"affinity is limited to cores running in non-SMT mode. If a task which "
"requested L1D flushing is scheduled on a SMT-enabled core the kernel sends a "
"SIGBUS to the task."
msgstr ""
